Argentina will tell its creditorsit needs an extension of deadlines for payment of capital andinterest on its 50 billion dlr foreign debt, Industry andForeign Trade Secretary Roberto Lavagna told reporters.    "We, the developing countries, are going to insist on theapplication of contingency clauses, to extend deadlines for thepayment of capital as well as interest," he said.    He said this could bring about what he called a possibleautomatic capitalisation of those parts of debt interest thatcould not be paid and even the elimination of a portion of thedebt. REUTER&#3;